(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Trubbish and Garbodor
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Trubbish and Garbodor
body:
568: Trubbish

Whenever I hear of an old-time fan that hates the newer generations’ Pokemon designs, this is easily one of the first Pokemon to come to mind right here. Once the Japanese versions of Black and White dropped and the whole Pokedex of new Pokemon started pouring out onto the internet, many may have garnered ire but none as much as the two Pokemon in this line, Trubbish and Garbodor. At least at first. Thank god, given a few months/years and a handful of people that liked the thing at first sight that the fandom now more or less loves Trubbish. And it deserves every little bit of love!!

And there’s very few fictional creatures that surpass the “rancid monster with a cute demeanor” look for me than Trubbish here. Like, I’m legit struggling to think up a flaw for this lil fella. The adorable wide-eyed face with some goofy teeth, the goomba-like body shape, the trash bag handles as floppy ears. And the bursting, overflowing garbage for arms. Every little bit of Trubbish is objectively wonderful. Errrr, here’s one! It’s always bugged me that the handles aren’t properly tied together. Kills the illusion just a little bit. But even then, that’s just a nitpick. Trubbish is fantastic and to anybody that still hates it in 2018, I diagnose you with BAD OPINION.

Personal Score: 9/10

Precious trash son.

569: Garbodor

And while I have written that first paragraph there, it’s mostly only true for Trubbish. At least, as far as I’ve seen, Trubbish is the one that gets most of the praise these days. Garbodor gets slightly more ignored than Trubbish, or it’s to this day still being hated on for really awful reasons. Often being a Pokemon to pop up on “Top 10 Worst Pokemon Designs” videos. To which I say SHAME.

I always see complaints about Pokemon based on inanimate objects being the worst in the series because “there’s no imagination!” or “that’s just stupid!” And. At least if you’ve been reading for a decent time now, y'all know me. I like my foxes, deers, and dragons as much as the next guy. But I wouldn’t call them “imaginative.” Garbodor keeps getting the criticism that it’s a design with little thought put into it, but I’d say the opposite were true if every other Pokemon were like Lycanroc or Glaceon. Obviously not to point fingers and say neither of those two had any effort put into them, but really? Ice dog and Rock dog get a free pass but the ridiculously weird and abnormal Garbodor is “unoriginal”?

Besides. You absolute clowns. Garbodor IS an animal! See how its body is made up of primarily some brown junk? And considering Trubbish’s “ears”, as well as Garbodor’s? AND its Japanese name is Dustdas? These two are literal, giant dust bunnies! Trash rabbits! And that’s just wonderful.

As you can probably tell, I like Garbodor’s design a lot. Give me a good sentient trash monster and I’ll (thankfully not literally) eat that right up. And even in a monster trope I like, Garbodor is the most quintessential out of all of them. It has a great face, wide-eyed and with a gaping mouth and some teeth no doubt made of contaminated, sharp scrap metal. The pink and blue bits are sadly kinda indistinguishable pieces of trash that you can’t really pick out as anything, really. Pieces of plastic? Maybe.

And probably one of my more favorite details about it is that this trash monster appears to use some huge, metal wires as a skeleton. And that skeleton is even visible from its left arm, poking through the trash. And for a heap monster, it would make sense for them to adapt something like those metal wires to use as a skeleton to help hold their shape. That, along with creating some cool asymmetry any self-respecting junk heap creature would have.

Personal Score: 9.5/10

These two are 200% friends

Overall:

[Archive]
